cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with scheduling policies for multihop wireless networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses mean field theory techniques to analyze the performance of the proposed scheduling policy, which is a common tool in information theory. 
3. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper proposes a distributed scheduling policy, which can be considered as a multiagent system. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with controlling congestion in wireless networks, which can be considered as a system control problem. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a distributed scheduling policy for wireless networks, which falls under the scope of distributed computing.
